1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:04,045
<i>Good evening, Doc.</i>
<i>May we see your ID?</i>

2
00:00:04,129 --> 00:00:05,255
[MILA] <i>Uh…</i>

3
00:00:05,338 --> 00:00:09,050
<i>Sir, uh, we need access</i>
<i>to the patient in Room 209</i>

4
00:00:09,134 --> 00:00:11,845
<i>because she has to be sent to the OR.</i>

5
00:00:11,928 --> 00:00:13,054
<i>It's really urgent.</i>

6
00:00:19,602 --> 00:00:23,440
<i>Come on. Let's just go this way.</i>
<i>We need to bring her to the OR right away.</i>

7
00:00:23,523 --> 00:00:25,775
[COP] <i>Why are you bringing her here?</i>
<i>Is the patient--</i>

8
00:00:25,859 --> 00:00:27,694
- [MUFFLED GUNSHOTS]
- [MILA WHIMPERS]

9
00:00:28,570 --> 00:00:30,405
<i>Come on, let's go!</i>

10
00:00:30,488 --> 00:00:31,573
<i>Move!</i>

11
00:00:33,450 --> 00:00:34,325
[GRUNTS]

12
00:00:34,701 --> 00:00:36,202
[MUFFLED GUNSHOT]

13
00:00:37,245 --> 00:00:38,329
<i>Where's Fredo?</i>

14
00:00:38,913 --> 00:00:40,457
<i>Someone saw us. He chased them.</i>

15
00:00:41,916 --> 00:00:45,044
[BLOWS LANDING,
FREDO AND LIAM GROANING]

16
00:00:46,004 --> 00:00:48,465
<i>Have you all lost your minds?</i>

17
00:00:48,548 --> 00:00:51,217
<i>Don't you realize how many cops are here?</i>

18
00:00:51,301 --> 00:00:54,345
<i>The police won't touch us</i>
<i>if we take people hostage.</i>

19
00:00:54,429 --> 00:00:59,309
<i>Once we capture the Rojas, the senator</i>
<i>and his son, and the whole hospital,</i>

20
00:00:59,392 --> 00:01:01,561
<i>we'll get everything we want.</i>

21
00:01:01,644 --> 00:01:02,937
[ALARM BLARING]

22
00:01:03,021 --> 00:01:04,939
[EMIL] <i>Go now, quick!</i>

23
00:01:06,608 --> 00:01:08,193
<i>Leni, get back here!</i>

24
00:01:08,276 --> 00:01:10,278
<i>I need to talk to Papa.</i>

25
00:01:10,361 --> 00:01:12,781
<i>Pa, I'm begging you. Stop this.</i>

26
00:01:13,948 --> 00:01:19,204
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [PEOPLE SCREAMING]

27
00:01:23,625 --> 00:01:26,211
[ALARM BLARING]

28
00:01:26,294 --> 00:01:29,088
Nurse, any update about the CT scan?

29
00:01:29,172 --> 00:01:30,298
Just a moment, please.

30
00:01:32,258 --> 00:01:38,681
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

31
00:01:40,558 --> 00:01:42,519
- What's that?
- We need to leave now, Ma.

32
00:01:42,602 --> 00:01:44,604
- What's happening?
- Let's find out.

33
00:01:44,687 --> 00:01:47,398
- What's going on?
- Ma.

34
00:01:49,109 --> 00:01:52,529
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING,
INDISTINCT SHOUTING]

35
00:01:55,949 --> 00:01:57,492
- [COP 1] This way!
- [VISITOR] Hurry!

36
00:01:57,575 --> 00:01:59,994
- [COP 2] Faster, faster!
- Come on!

37
00:02:00,078 --> 00:02:04,499
Quick, quick, quick! Let's go, move it!

38
00:02:04,582 --> 00:02:06,251
[ALARM CONTINUES TO BLARE]

39
00:02:06,334 --> 00:02:08,586
Boss Emil, this is Fredo.

40
00:02:08,670 --> 00:02:10,004
Fredo?

41
00:02:10,088 --> 00:02:11,297
What's happening?

42
00:02:11,381 --> 00:02:13,133
I'm at the main entrance, boss.

43
00:02:13,716 --> 00:02:14,884
<i>It's getting chaotic here.</i>

44
00:02:14,968 --> 00:02:17,846
A lot of people are going outside.
Police officers are coming in.

45
00:02:17,929 --> 00:02:19,222
[COP 2] Hey!

46
00:02:19,931 --> 00:02:22,100
Hey, where are you going?!
Over here!

47
00:02:22,183 --> 00:02:26,104
- [MUSIC INTENSIFIES]
- [CROWD CLAMORING]

48
00:02:26,771 --> 00:02:28,815
The police are aware of us now.

49
00:02:30,066 --> 00:02:30,900
Mila!

50
00:02:30,984 --> 00:02:31,860
Boss.

51
00:02:32,569 --> 00:02:34,279
What room is the senator's son in?

52
00:02:35,280 --> 00:02:36,364
[BREATH QUIVERS]

53
00:02:36,447 --> 00:02:38,158
Out with it.

54
00:02:38,908 --> 00:02:40,368
Room 359.

55
00:02:41,161 --> 00:02:42,954
- Conrad, Roman.
- Boss.

56
00:02:43,538 --> 00:02:46,207
Get to the senator's son.

57
00:02:46,291 --> 00:02:47,375
- Move it!
- Copy!

58
00:02:47,458 --> 00:02:49,294
Bring those crates, we're taking them now.

59
00:02:49,377 --> 00:02:54,090
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

60
00:02:54,173 --> 00:02:55,341
Come on!

61
00:02:57,343 --> 00:02:58,803
Stop this, Pa.

62
00:03:06,436 --> 00:03:13,276
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

63
00:03:42,222 --> 00:03:44,015
Look at the lovebirds over here.

64
00:03:44,098 --> 00:03:45,725
I'm kind of jealous.

65
00:03:45,808 --> 00:03:47,143
[MACKY, EDUARDO CHUCKLE]

66
00:03:47,227 --> 00:03:51,189
- I'll just get that.
- I'm glad the fire alarm stopped.

67
00:03:53,566 --> 00:03:56,444
Maybe it was just a drill,
or a false alarm.

68
00:03:56,527 --> 00:03:57,654
Probably.

69
00:03:58,446 --> 00:03:59,614
- Come on.
- Thank you, Dad.

70
00:03:59,697 --> 00:04:00,823
Sure. Now, go on and eat.

71
00:04:00,907 --> 00:04:02,408
- You should eat too.
- Go ahead.

72
00:04:03,701 --> 00:04:05,745
Help him eat so that--

73
00:04:05,828 --> 00:04:08,122
[PEOPLE START SCREAMING OUTSIDE]

74
00:04:08,206 --> 00:04:09,415
What's going on?

75
00:04:09,499 --> 00:04:11,542
- Sir, remain inside for now.
- Why?

76
00:04:11,626 --> 00:04:13,044
There's a gunman roaming the hospital.

77
00:04:13,127 --> 00:04:15,713
- What? Who?
- [DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

78
00:04:15,797 --> 00:04:18,758
We're not sure yet, sir.
But it's safer for us if we stay in.

79
00:04:18,841 --> 00:04:22,262
[CROWD CLAMORING IN THE DISTANCE]

80
00:04:22,345 --> 00:04:23,680
Stay here.

81
00:04:29,310 --> 00:04:30,478
[MAN 1] We need to run!

82
00:04:30,561 --> 00:04:32,188
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

83
00:04:32,272 --> 00:04:34,399
- [MAN 1] Everyone, run!
- [MAN 2] Sorry!

84
00:04:34,482 --> 00:04:35,650
[MAN 3] Guard!

85
00:04:36,818 --> 00:04:38,027
[WOMAN 1] Let's go now!

86
00:04:39,070 --> 00:04:40,905
[NURSE] Hey, hey! Follow me!

87
00:04:40,989 --> 00:04:43,866
[FRANTIC MURMURING]

88
00:04:43,950 --> 00:04:45,034
- [GRETA] Liam! Liam, son!
- Ma!

89
00:04:45,118 --> 00:04:46,828
- I've been looking for you.
- We need to go.

90
00:04:46,911 --> 00:04:48,955
Why? The fire alarm already stopped.

91
00:04:49,038 --> 00:04:50,498
What we talked about earlier? I'm not--

92
00:04:50,581 --> 00:04:52,625
- We'll talk later.
- Why? What's going on?

93
00:04:52,709 --> 00:04:54,585
Emil Padua and his men are alive.

94
00:04:54,669 --> 00:04:56,879
- They're here in the hospital!
- [GRETA WHIMPERS]

95
00:04:56,963 --> 00:04:58,548
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

96
00:04:58,631 --> 00:05:02,260
- [LUCAS CLICKING TONGUE]
- [NERVOUS BREATHS]

97
00:05:02,343 --> 00:05:04,679
[LIAM BREATHING HEAVILY]

98
00:05:07,765 --> 00:05:08,641
[GRUNTS WEAKLY]

99
00:05:08,725 --> 00:05:12,770
- [MAN 4] We need help!
- [WOMAN 2] Somebody help us!

100
00:05:12,854 --> 00:05:14,022
Help!

101
00:05:14,105 --> 00:05:18,484
- [DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [INDISTINCT SHOUTING]

102
00:05:20,570 --> 00:05:22,196
[CROWD SCREAMING IN FEAR]

103
00:05:22,280 --> 00:05:24,157
Sir, please remain in your room.

104
00:05:24,240 --> 00:05:26,075
- Go inside for now.
- What?

105
00:05:26,159 --> 00:05:28,119
- [WOMAN 3] Help us!
- [WOMAN 4] Please help!

106
00:05:28,202 --> 00:05:29,912
- Hang on.
- He's going to kill us!

107
00:05:29,996 --> 00:05:31,831
- [WOMAN 3 SOBS]
- What did she say?

108
00:05:31,914 --> 00:05:33,916
There's a gunman inside the building.
But don't worry.

109
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,210
Police and hospital security
are chasing him.

110
00:05:36,294 --> 00:05:38,546
Please, go back inside your room.

111
00:05:38,629 --> 00:05:41,257
- [OVERLAPPING SHOUTING, CRYING]
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

112
00:05:41,340 --> 00:05:42,842
- [MAN 5] Come on!
- [WOMAN 5] Hey, officer!

113
00:05:42,925 --> 00:05:44,260
What's going on?

114
00:05:46,304 --> 00:05:47,555
[WOMEN YELPING, WHIMPERING]

115
00:05:47,638 --> 00:05:49,724
- Let's get out of here!
- Our patients!

116
00:05:49,807 --> 00:05:52,185
- Move them out now!
- Get the patients out!

117
00:05:52,935 --> 00:05:53,936
[MAGNUS GROANS]

118
00:05:56,189 --> 00:05:57,899
You made things harder for me.

119
00:05:57,982 --> 00:05:59,859
- I thought--
- That we were dead?

120
00:06:01,069 --> 00:06:02,487
Not yet.

121
00:06:03,571 --> 00:06:05,656
We've still got work to do.

122
00:06:05,740 --> 00:06:07,325
[SINISTER MUSIC PLAYING]

123
00:06:07,408 --> 00:06:08,910
- [PHONE BEEPS]
- [LINE RINGING]

124
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:17,543
[PHONE RINGING]

125
00:06:20,797 --> 00:06:21,964
Boss Emil.

126
00:06:22,924 --> 00:06:23,883
I have Liam

127
00:06:23,966 --> 00:06:25,510
<i>and Greta Roja with me.</i>

128
00:06:25,593 --> 00:06:28,846
[SINISTER MUSIC CONTINUES]

129
00:06:28,930 --> 00:06:30,348
Take them up.

130
00:06:31,099 --> 00:06:32,141
We're coming.

131
00:06:33,142 --> 00:06:34,018
[CALL ENDS]

132
00:06:43,236 --> 00:06:45,196
- [MUFFLED GUNSHOTS]
- [BODY THUDS]

133
00:06:45,863 --> 00:06:47,115
[GASPING]

134
00:06:47,198 --> 00:06:49,575
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

135
00:06:49,659 --> 00:06:50,827
Sweetie,

136
00:06:50,910 --> 00:06:53,871
you shouldn't have come with us.

137
00:06:53,955 --> 00:06:58,042
But don't worry.
I'll have them look out for you.

138
00:06:58,668 --> 00:07:00,169
- Gwen, Homer.
- Boss.

139
00:07:00,253 --> 00:07:02,547
- Boss.
- Remember what we talked about.

140
00:07:02,630 --> 00:07:04,257
Take care of my daughter.

141
00:07:04,882 --> 00:07:05,925
Yes, boss.

142
00:07:06,008 --> 00:07:08,052
Mila, come with us. We need you.

143
00:07:08,136 --> 00:07:09,512
Wait, what about my husband?

144
00:07:09,595 --> 00:07:11,472
He can take care of himself.

145
00:07:11,556 --> 00:07:13,349
- Dado.
- Boss?

146
00:07:15,101 --> 00:07:21,732
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

147
00:07:26,028 --> 00:07:28,865
Son, someone's shooting people back there!

148
00:07:28,948 --> 00:07:30,908
What matters is we get out of here, okay?

149
00:07:30,992 --> 00:07:33,828
- [WENDY, WOMAN 6 BREATHING HEAVILY]
- [OLSEN] Come on!

150
00:07:33,911 --> 00:07:37,206
[HURRIED FOOTSTEPS]

151
00:07:38,708 --> 00:07:40,418
[LUCAS] Whoa, whoa, whoa.

152
00:07:40,501 --> 00:07:41,919
There.

153
00:07:42,003 --> 00:07:43,337
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

154
00:07:43,421 --> 00:07:45,590
Boss Emil is on his way.

155
00:07:45,673 --> 00:07:47,425
Keep walking, okay?

156
00:07:48,050 --> 00:07:49,469
Just keep walking.

157
00:07:50,303 --> 00:07:52,847
Take it easy.

158
00:07:56,267 --> 00:07:58,060
Go on, walk some more.

159
00:07:58,686 --> 00:07:59,854
Pick up the pace.

160
00:07:59,937 --> 00:08:01,314
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

161
00:08:01,397 --> 00:08:03,941
That's right, keep walking.

162
00:08:04,025 --> 00:08:05,902
Slow and steady.

163
00:08:05,985 --> 00:08:08,446
Put one foot in front of the other.

164
00:08:08,529 --> 00:08:10,823
Let's make a left turn now.

165
00:08:12,992 --> 00:08:14,952
Liam, up you go.

166
00:08:15,578 --> 00:08:16,871
[GASPS]

167
00:08:16,954 --> 00:08:19,874
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

168
00:08:19,957 --> 00:08:21,209
[LUCAS] Climb up.

169
00:08:21,292 --> 00:08:23,044
Good boy.

170
00:08:27,673 --> 00:08:29,217
[LUCAS] You're doing great.

171
00:08:29,300 --> 00:08:32,261
[MUSIC BECOMES DRAMATIC]

172
00:08:32,345 --> 00:08:33,971
Hey! What are you doing, son?

173
00:08:34,055 --> 00:08:35,973
Mama, I need to help them.

174
00:08:36,057 --> 00:08:38,726
- No, you don't! Just come with me!
- Mama, call--

175
00:08:38,809 --> 00:08:40,436
- Let's get out of here!
- Call the cops.

176
00:08:40,520 --> 00:08:42,522
Tell them to reach the fire exit.

177
00:08:42,605 --> 00:08:44,315
Do that, and then leave this place.

178
00:08:44,398 --> 00:08:46,400
Please! Go on, Mama!

179
00:08:46,484 --> 00:08:47,652
[LOUD THWACK]

180
00:08:47,735 --> 00:08:52,865
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

181
00:08:52,949 --> 00:08:55,243
[HEAVY BREATHS, HUFFS]

182
00:08:55,326 --> 00:08:56,244
[EXCLAIMS]

183
00:08:57,078 --> 00:09:01,290
[THRILLING MUSIC PLAYING]

184
00:09:04,293 --> 00:09:08,172
Ma'am Happy, aren't we leaving yet?

185
00:09:08,256 --> 00:09:09,799
[HAPPY] That was nothing!

186
00:09:10,591 --> 00:09:12,426
Are you hearing anything?
The fire alarm is off.

187
00:09:12,510 --> 00:09:13,469
Why should we leave?

188
00:09:15,179 --> 00:09:18,766
But come to think of it,
you do have a point, Joy.

189
00:09:18,849 --> 00:09:22,144
Let's go now and escape our debt.

190
00:09:22,228 --> 00:09:25,606
The hospital fees are beyond unreasonable.

191
00:09:25,690 --> 00:09:26,774
Mm-hmm.

192
00:09:26,857 --> 00:09:28,401
Whatever. Let's go.

193
00:09:29,610 --> 00:09:30,695
No need to convince me.

194
00:09:30,778 --> 00:09:31,779
- Come on.
- I know--

195
00:09:32,363 --> 00:09:33,698
- [GUNSHOT]
- [BODY THUDS]

196
00:09:33,781 --> 00:09:40,371
- [ALL SCREAMING IN FEAR]
- [SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

197
00:09:41,080 --> 00:09:42,331
Out of my way!

198
00:09:42,415 --> 00:09:44,959
- My goodness!
- This can't be happening!

199
00:09:45,042 --> 00:09:47,420
[OFFICER] There's no need to panic!
Everyone will make it out alive!

200
00:09:47,503 --> 00:09:48,546
[JOY] Where do we go?

201
00:09:48,629 --> 00:09:50,089
- [WOMAN 7] Hurry!
- Let's go!

202
00:09:50,172 --> 00:09:52,592
- [SOBS] Oh no…
- [WOMAN 8] Come on, faster!

203
00:09:52,675 --> 00:09:53,884
[HAPPY, JOY SOBBING]

204
00:09:53,968 --> 00:09:56,762
- Let's leave now!
- Yes, yes…

205
00:09:56,846 --> 00:10:00,850
- [SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [WOMEN SOBBING]

206
00:10:00,933 --> 00:10:03,019
[SCREAMING]

207
00:10:03,102 --> 00:10:05,396
- [GLASS BREAKS]
- [JOY WAILS]

208
00:10:05,479 --> 00:10:09,525
- Joy! Joy, let's go!
- I can't!

209
00:10:09,609 --> 00:10:13,362
Joy! Hold on to me, Joy!

210
00:10:13,446 --> 00:10:15,323
Joy, come here!

211
00:10:15,406 --> 00:10:17,867
Don't leave me here!

212
00:10:17,950 --> 00:10:19,702
[JOY WAILING]

213
00:10:19,785 --> 00:10:21,454
- [JOY] Ma'am Happy!
- Joy!

214
00:10:22,413 --> 00:10:23,372
Joy!

215
00:10:23,456 --> 00:10:25,833
- Help Joy out!
- Ma'am!

216
00:10:25,916 --> 00:10:29,962
- Hold on to me. We need to go!
- [ICE] Come on.

217
00:10:30,046 --> 00:10:32,423
- Where are we going?
- [FIN] Let's just move!

218
00:10:32,506 --> 00:10:35,426
- Hurry up! This way!
- [SOBBING]

219
00:10:35,509 --> 00:10:37,303
There, inside!

220
00:10:37,386 --> 00:10:39,930
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

221
00:10:40,014 --> 00:10:42,475
The security detail at the hospital
isn't responding.

222
00:10:42,558 --> 00:10:45,478
Go outside and find out what's happening!

223
00:10:45,561 --> 00:10:46,979
Yes, sir!

224
00:10:48,689 --> 00:10:50,775
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [MACKY YELLS]

225
00:10:50,858 --> 00:10:53,402
- [PANICKED BREATHS]
- Senator Maristella.

226
00:10:53,486 --> 00:10:55,863
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

227
00:10:55,946 --> 00:10:59,450
Sir Emil is sending you
a cordial invitation.

228
00:10:59,533 --> 00:11:00,576
[DOOR CLOSES]

229
00:11:06,207 --> 00:11:11,253
- [EDUARDO SHOUTING]
- Shut up! Try to speak another word!

230
00:11:12,505 --> 00:11:13,964
Try me!

231
00:11:14,590 --> 00:11:17,760
- [STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [ELEVATOR DINGS]

232
00:11:18,594 --> 00:11:20,679
[SCREAMS]

233
00:11:22,807 --> 00:11:24,433
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

234
00:11:24,517 --> 00:11:25,976
Get down!

235
00:11:26,602 --> 00:11:28,687
Hurry up!

236
00:11:30,314 --> 00:11:33,818
[WENDY] They have Greta Roja
and Liam Roja!

237
00:11:33,901 --> 00:11:36,862
They were at the fire exit
near the chapel.

238
00:11:36,946 --> 00:11:39,156
- Please go after them!
- Let's move!

239
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:40,950
Wendy, Wendy!

240
00:11:41,575 --> 00:11:44,120
- They have Greta and Liam!
- Who are they?

241
00:11:44,203 --> 00:11:46,247
I think it's

242
00:11:46,330 --> 00:11:47,748
Emil Padua?

243
00:11:47,832 --> 00:11:49,667
- He was with…
- [NURSE SHOUTING] Move!

244
00:11:49,750 --> 00:11:52,837
- Olsen! Where is he?
- Move!

245
00:11:52,920 --> 00:11:54,630
- Where's Olsen?
- Wendy!

246
00:11:54,713 --> 00:11:55,881
Olsen!

247
00:11:55,965 --> 00:11:58,843
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

248
00:11:58,926 --> 00:11:59,885
[WENDY] Olsen!

249
00:12:00,511 --> 00:12:01,887
Hurry up!

250
00:12:01,971 --> 00:12:05,474
Your mother's so slow.
Tell her to hurry up!

251
00:12:05,558 --> 00:12:07,393
Hurry up!

252
00:12:08,936 --> 00:12:14,859
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYS]

253
00:12:15,943 --> 00:12:19,447
[GRUNTING]

254
00:12:20,030 --> 00:12:26,454
[GROANING]

255
00:12:30,958 --> 00:12:37,590
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

256
00:12:38,382 --> 00:12:39,425
[GROWLS]

257
00:12:40,384 --> 00:12:44,972
[BREATHING SHAKILY]

258
00:12:45,055 --> 00:12:47,600
[GRUNTING]

259
00:12:49,894 --> 00:12:51,145
Stay back!

260
00:12:52,271 --> 00:12:55,691
Put down that gun!

261
00:12:55,774 --> 00:12:57,443
Or we'll all explode!

262
00:12:58,027 --> 00:12:59,945
Go there!

263
00:13:00,029 --> 00:13:01,864
Hurry up!

264
00:13:01,947 --> 00:13:08,954
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

265
00:13:11,749 --> 00:13:14,418
- [GRUNTS]
- [GRENADE PIN CLINKS]

266
00:13:14,502 --> 00:13:17,755
- [OLSEN YELLS]
- [EXPLOSION]

267
00:13:17,838 --> 00:13:19,840
[GROANING]

268
00:13:19,924 --> 00:13:24,595
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

269
00:13:24,678 --> 00:13:31,018
[CROWD SHOUTING]

270
00:13:31,977 --> 00:13:33,896
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

271
00:13:33,979 --> 00:13:35,648
[DISTANT GUNSHOTS]

272
00:13:36,482 --> 00:13:37,900
[MAGNUS] Wendy!

273
00:13:37,983 --> 00:13:39,818
[WENDY PANTING] Olsen!

274
00:13:44,532 --> 00:13:48,035
[HIGH-PITCHED RINGING]

275
00:13:48,953 --> 00:13:54,959
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

276
00:13:59,004 --> 00:14:00,881
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

277
00:14:00,965 --> 00:14:02,091
[COUGHS]

278
00:14:04,051 --> 00:14:05,427
Okay.

279
00:14:05,511 --> 00:14:06,971
Please be careful.

280
00:14:08,264 --> 00:14:09,974
Doc, what did they say?

281
00:14:10,975 --> 00:14:13,227
Luna, the hospital is in lockdown.

282
00:14:13,310 --> 00:14:15,688
There are armed men who
are inside the premises.

283
00:14:15,771 --> 00:14:18,857
Luckily, I talked with
the nurse who just got out.

284
00:14:18,941 --> 00:14:20,734
Police officers have now arrived.

285
00:14:20,818 --> 00:14:23,320
They've identified the gunman.

286
00:14:23,404 --> 00:14:25,865
The criminal is the same one
who was at La Playa Roja.

287
00:14:25,948 --> 00:14:27,074
Huh?

288
00:14:27,658 --> 00:14:29,910
That's impossible.

289
00:14:29,994 --> 00:14:31,912
They're all dead already!

290
00:14:31,996 --> 00:14:33,372
No, Luna.

291
00:14:33,873 --> 00:14:35,833
The police have confirmed it.

292
00:14:35,916 --> 00:14:37,293
They're alive.

293
00:14:37,376 --> 00:14:38,836
No.

294
00:14:38,919 --> 00:14:39,962
This can't be.

295
00:14:40,045 --> 00:14:41,297
Luna.

296
00:14:42,464 --> 00:14:43,424
It's dangerous.

297
00:14:43,507 --> 00:14:46,385
The police are now
hunting those criminals.

298
00:14:46,969 --> 00:14:48,679
Gunshots could be exchanged.

299
00:14:49,972 --> 00:14:52,057
My friends need me.

300
00:14:52,141 --> 00:14:53,559
Doc.

301
00:14:53,642 --> 00:14:55,853
My friends are in danger.

302
00:14:55,936 --> 00:14:57,813
They need my help.

303
00:14:57,897 --> 00:15:03,652
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

304
00:15:14,914 --> 00:15:15,915
Come on.

305
00:15:18,459 --> 00:15:20,085
- [LENI BREATHES FAINTLY]
- [THUDS]

306
00:15:20,169 --> 00:15:26,675
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

307
00:15:31,931 --> 00:15:34,475
Her temperature's still high.
Her fever could've relapsed.

308
00:15:34,558 --> 00:15:36,769
I don't know what to do.
I'm not a real nurse!

309
00:15:36,852 --> 00:15:39,521
I know. That's why we
need to find a doctor.

310
00:15:39,605 --> 00:15:41,190
Mila, come with me. Let's find a doctor.

311
00:15:41,273 --> 00:15:43,943
I need to go to my husband.

312
00:15:44,026 --> 00:15:46,153
Mila! Mila!

313
00:15:46,236 --> 00:15:49,198
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

314
00:15:49,281 --> 00:15:50,574
I'll take care of it.

315
00:15:54,161 --> 00:15:55,371
[DOOR CLOSES]

316
00:15:56,664 --> 00:16:00,209
For all we know,
they've already left with their families.

317
00:16:00,292 --> 00:16:02,419
You don't know my friend.

318
00:16:02,503 --> 00:16:06,173
Liam wouldn't leave
knowing I'm still here.

319
00:16:06,966 --> 00:16:08,175
The same goes for me.

320
00:16:08,258 --> 00:16:11,804
Neither of us would leave until we
knew the other was safe.

321
00:16:11,887 --> 00:16:13,597
Because we're best friends.

322
00:16:13,681 --> 00:16:15,391
Are you really best friends?

323
00:16:16,517 --> 00:16:18,519
What are you trying to say, Doc?

324
00:16:19,520 --> 00:16:20,813
Go back there.

325
00:16:20,896 --> 00:16:22,356
I said no!

326
00:16:22,439 --> 00:16:24,525
Where are you going to look for them?

327
00:16:24,608 --> 00:16:26,527
Can you handle those criminals?

328
00:16:26,610 --> 00:16:29,196
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

329
00:16:29,279 --> 00:16:30,656
If you only knew.

330
00:16:33,033 --> 00:16:33,867
Luna--

331
00:16:33,951 --> 00:16:35,536
[GRUNTS]

332
00:16:35,619 --> 00:16:38,580
- Sorry, Doc.
- [GROANS]

333
00:16:38,664 --> 00:16:42,501
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

334
00:16:42,584 --> 00:16:43,627
[TENSE MUSIC FADES]

335
00:16:44,628 --> 00:16:46,755
[GWEN] Doc, wait. Doc.

336
00:16:46,839 --> 00:16:48,465
Everyone already evacuated,

337
00:16:48,549 --> 00:16:50,384
including my friend's doctor.

338
00:16:50,467 --> 00:16:51,760
He left her alone.

339
00:16:51,844 --> 00:16:54,096
Can you help my friend?

340
00:16:55,889 --> 00:16:58,475
I'd give you a five-star rating, but…

341
00:16:59,393 --> 00:17:01,186
<i>the sauce of the steak wasn't good.</i>

342
00:17:01,895 --> 00:17:07,818
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

343
00:17:10,988 --> 00:17:12,614
- Where is she?
- This way, Doc.

344
00:17:27,463 --> 00:17:29,923
[LIAM GRUNTS, COUGHS]

345
00:17:30,716 --> 00:17:31,675
[GROANS]

346
00:17:31,759 --> 00:17:34,678
- Ma. Ma.
- [GRETA WHIMPERING]

347
00:17:34,762 --> 00:17:36,221
Are you okay, Ma?

348
00:17:36,305 --> 00:17:38,807
- Mm-hmm.
- Olsen.

349
00:17:40,309 --> 00:17:42,019
Olsen. [GRUNTS]

350
00:17:42,102 --> 00:17:43,479
Olsen.

351
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:46,273
- Dude. Dude.
- Liam…

352
00:17:46,356 --> 00:17:48,067
Hey! Dude! Wake up!

353
00:17:48,150 --> 00:17:50,611
- Dude. Hey!
- Let's go.

354
00:17:50,694 --> 00:17:54,406
- I won't leave him, Ma. I won't!
- Let's go. There's nothing we can do.

355
00:17:54,490 --> 00:17:56,700
Let's go. We need to go--

356
00:17:56,784 --> 00:17:58,077
You told me yourself, remember?

357
00:17:58,160 --> 00:17:59,787
That Olsen might be my brother?

358
00:17:59,870 --> 00:18:03,665
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

359
00:18:03,749 --> 00:18:06,001
[LIAM] Dude, come on. Let's go.

360
00:18:06,085 --> 00:18:07,461
We need to go, dude.

361
00:18:07,544 --> 00:18:10,130
[LIAM GRUNTS]

362
00:18:11,048 --> 00:18:13,258
- [LIAM GROANS]
- [OLSEN GRUNTS, COUGHS]

363
00:18:13,342 --> 00:18:15,010
- [OLSEN COUGHS]
- [LIAM GRUNTS]

364
00:18:16,678 --> 00:18:18,555
[OLSEN RETCHES, COUGHS]

365
00:18:19,181 --> 00:18:20,974
[OLSEN GRUNTS]

366
00:18:21,058 --> 00:18:23,143
[COUGHING]

367
00:18:23,811 --> 00:18:27,606
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

368
00:18:27,689 --> 00:18:29,108
No one is leaving.

369
00:18:29,191 --> 00:18:30,692
[LIAM, OLSEN PANTS]

370
00:18:31,527 --> 00:18:35,447
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

371
00:18:35,531 --> 00:18:37,950
You killed my grandpa! Damn you!

372
00:18:38,033 --> 00:18:40,327
- [OLSEN GRUNTS]
- [GRETA SCREAMS] No!

373
00:18:40,410 --> 00:18:43,247
Keep your friend in check
if you want him to live.

374
00:18:43,831 --> 00:18:45,916
- Bro, enough. Stop.
- [OLSEN GRUNTS]

375
00:18:50,087 --> 00:18:51,630
Lucas, are you okay?

376
00:18:54,591 --> 00:18:57,136
- Stand up!
- Stand!

377
00:18:58,345 --> 00:18:59,930
[EMIL] Get up!

378
00:19:00,013 --> 00:19:02,099
[OLSEN COUGHS]

379
00:19:02,182 --> 00:19:03,809
[GRETA GRUNTS]

380
00:19:03,892 --> 00:19:05,769
- [OLSEN GRUNTS]
- [DADO] Walk!

381
00:19:08,605 --> 00:19:09,898
[EMIL] Walk!

382
00:19:09,982 --> 00:19:15,320
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

383
00:19:19,449 --> 00:19:20,325
<i>What's happening?</i>

384
00:19:20,409 --> 00:19:23,078
<i>A lot of people are going outside.</i>
<i>Police officers are coming in.</i>

385
00:19:23,579 --> 00:19:24,663
<i>Hey!</i>

386
00:19:24,746 --> 00:19:27,499
<i>- What room is the senator's son in?</i>
- [MILA]<i> Room 359.</i>

387
00:19:27,583 --> 00:19:29,710
[REPORTER] <i>It has been confirmed</i>
<i>that the hostage takers</i>

388
00:19:29,793 --> 00:19:32,796
<i>have Senator Eduardo Maristella,</i>
<i>Macky Maristella,</i>

389
00:19:32,880 --> 00:19:35,549
<i>Greta Roja, and her son, Liam Roja.</i>

390
00:19:35,632 --> 00:19:37,676
<i>My friends are in danger.</i>

391
00:19:37,759 --> 00:19:39,219
<i>They need my help.</i>

392
00:19:39,303 --> 00:19:40,888
<i>Can you handle those criminals?</i>

393
00:19:40,971 --> 00:19:42,973
[JOY CRIES]

394
00:19:43,056 --> 00:19:44,516
<i>Joy! Joy!</i>

395
00:19:44,600 --> 00:19:47,728
<i>Joy! Hold onto me, Joy!</i>

396
00:19:47,811 --> 00:19:49,146
<i>Olsen!</i>

397
00:19:49,229 --> 00:19:50,939
<i>Wendy, Emil has a big grudge against me.</i>

398
00:19:51,023 --> 00:19:54,484
<i>If something happens to Olsen,</i>
<i>it would be because of you?!</i>

399
00:19:54,568 --> 00:19:56,570
<i>I treat Olsen like my own kid.</i>

400
00:19:56,653 --> 00:19:59,698
<i>There's a possibility that he's my son.</i>
<i>Be honest with me!</i>

401
00:19:59,781 --> 00:20:01,992
[DADO] <i>Don't try to remove that.</i>

402
00:20:02,075 --> 00:20:05,120
<i>If you get more than 50 meters away,</i>
<i>this is what will happen to you.</i>

403
00:20:06,455 --> 00:20:08,123
- [EXPLOSION]
- [PEOPLE SCREAMING]

404
00:20:10,292 --> 00:20:12,252
<i>Do you think you can</i>
<i>get away with this again?</i>

405
00:20:12,336 --> 00:20:14,296
<i>We will get away with this.</i>

406
00:20:16,506 --> 00:20:18,008
- [GUNSHOT]
<i>- </i>[GROANS]

407
00:20:19,176 --> 00:20:21,053
[MINNIE] <i>Where will we pass through?</i>

408
00:20:21,136 --> 00:20:23,013
[BOMBS BEEPING]

409
00:20:23,096 --> 00:20:26,600
[EMIL] <i>Which of your two sons</i>
<i>are you going to choose to save,</i>

410
00:20:26,683 --> 00:20:29,937
<i>and which one will you leave to die?</i>

411
00:20:30,020 --> 00:20:33,607
<i>If you won't choose,</i>
<i>I'll push them both.</i>
